Dhaubanjar said he saw about 40 people rounded up by police Thursday night after Hyanju's beating death.
He said many belonged to the same Communist faction that Hyanju once supported.
"People started beating him with umbrellas," Dhaubanjar said.
"There were a lot of scratches on his body, and a lot of blood.
As Hyanju's body was taken through the winding streets of Bhaktapur, a 12th-century town of ancient Hindu temples, thousands of the town's 50,000 people jammed streets, temple steps and the balconies of brick and mud houses.
